    <main>
        <h2>Vision</h2>
        <p>"To be the excellent organization in Trincomalee District to create a Healthier Community that contributes towards a Healthier Nation"</p>

        <h2>Mission</h2>
        <p>"To Assure a Healthier Community by ensuring equitable access to sustainable quality healthcare service while promoting self-reliance, personal responsibility and healthy lifestyle in Trincomalee District"</p>

        <h2>Our Services</h2>
        <h3>Curative Care Services</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Planning of curative healthcare services under ministry guidance</li>
            <li>Implementing and monitoring of plans in consultation with PDHS</li>
            <li>Maintaining medical statistics and private sector regulation</li>
            <li>Support for emergency units, surveys, and coordination with MOH</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Preventive Health Services</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Planning, implementing, and monitoring preventive services</li>
            <li>Support for occupational and waterborne disease prevention</li>
            <li>Surveys, operational research, and coordination with MOH units</li>
            <li>Services provided through 12 MOH units and public health staff</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Other Services</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Maternal and Child Health:</strong> Antenatal, postnatal, immunization, growth monitoring</li>
            <li><strong>School Health:</strong> School dental and general health services</li>
            <li><strong>Well-women Services:</strong> Full medical check-ups and cancer screening</li>
            <li><strong>Family Planning:</strong> Free contraceptive methods and counseling</li>
            <li>Environmental & Occupational Health</li>
            <li>Prevention of Communicable & Non-Communicable Diseases</li>
            <li>Active Ageing, Mental Health & Health Promotion</li>
            <li>Oral and Dental Health Services</li>
        </ul>
    </main>

